We need a description of the assailant. 

49
00:03:05,004 --> 00:03:05,930
好把他拘捕归案
Let's get this guy off the street.

50
00:03:11,835 --> 00:03:13,602
约翰先生吗
Mr. John?

51
00:03:13,637 --> 00:03:15,370
我认识你吗
Do I know you?

52
00:03:15,405 --> 00:03:18,006
我是马龙医生 替警方工作
I'm Doctor Malone. I work with the police.

53
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,874
这位是韦涅夫斯基警探
This is Detective Wisnefski.

54
00:03:19,909 --> 00:03:23,042
我已经跟一位警官说过了
I already spoke to an officer. 

55
00:03:23,043 --> 00:03:25,079
我辩认不出他是谁
I cannot identify this man.

56
00:03:25,113 --> 00:03:26,581
我明白
I understand that.

57
00:03:26,615 --> 00:03:28,616
我看过你的档案摘要
I've read a summary of your file.

58
00:03:28,651 --> 00:03:31,853
你过去四年左右都是这个状态吗
You've had your condition for the last 4 years or so?

59
00:03:31,887 --> 00:03:34,321
我记不清有多久了
I cannot remember how long.

60
00:03:34,356 --> 00:03:36,623
你得去问我的医生
You'll have to ask my doctor.

61
00:03:36,658 --> 00:03:40,894
你能告诉我你望着我的时候看到的是什么吗
Can you tell me what you see when you look at me?

62
00:03:45,333 --> 00:03:49,069
我能看到你完整的面部
You have all the pieces of a face...

63
00:03:49,103 --> 00:03:51,571
鼻子
a nose,

64
00:03:51,605 --> 00:03:54,207
嘴巴
mouth...

65
00:03:54,241 --> 00:03:56,209
以及你的眼睛
and your eyes.

66
00:03:56,243 --> 00:03:59,546
你的眼睛非常特别
You have very unique eyes.

67
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:02,715
我或许认识你
I might recognize you.

68
00:04:02,749 --> 00:04:05,117
你是怎么处理这些信息的
How do you cope?

69
00:04:05,151 --> 00:04:06,685
我有医生
I have a doctor.

70
00:04:06,719 --> 00:04:10,789
他教我一些技巧 方法
He teaches me tricks, techniques.

71
00:04:10,823 --> 00:04:13,292
辅以声音 首饰
Voices help, jewellery,

72
00:04:13,326 --> 00:04:15,727
纹身
tattoos.

73
00:04:15,761 --> 00:04:19,364
我看你主要是看你的枪
I look at you and mainly I see your gun.

74
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:21,165
这也是我
It's how I would be

75
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,001
如果再次见到你最有可能认出你的方式
most likely to know you if I see you again.

76
00:04:24,035 --> 00:04:27,538
那个袭击了你的人 你注意到了他的什么
The man who attacked you, what did you notice about him?

77
00:04:30,642 --> 00:04:32,143
他的刀
His knife.

78
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:38,582
"我认识你" 或者 "你认识我"
"I know you" or "You know me".

79
00:04:38,616 --> 00:04:40,584
这就是目击者们声称他们听到的
That's what the witnesses said that they heard.

80
00:04:40,618 --> 00:04:42,586
有关于疑犯的描述吗
Any description of the suspect?

81
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:45,788
黑人男子 年龄在十八到四十五之间
Black male. I'm getting ages from 18 to 45,

82
00:04:45,823 --> 00:04:47,193
身高五尺八到六尺二之间 
height from 5'8 " to 6'2". 

83
00:04:47,194 --> 00:04:48,858
这么说 他们注意到了他是个黑人
So, they noticed he was black.

84
00:04:48,892 --> 00:04:50,994
正如所料 仅此而已
Figures. That's about all.

85
00:04:51,028 --> 00:04:54,062
跑这么老远 砍了艾德瑞斯约翰五刀
You go this far, you slash Idaris John 5 times.

86
00:04:54,097 --> 00:04:56,765
但却不足以杀死他 那么为何住手呢
Not much more to kill him. So, why stop?

87
00:04:56,799 --> 00:04:58,767
刺杀才致命
Stab wounds kill.

88
00:04:58,801 --> 00:05:00,469
他只是砍
He only slashed.

89
00:05:00,504 --> 00:05:03,205
你是什么 嗜血法医吗 你在看鲜血飞溅吗
What are you, Dexter? You're reading blood spatter?

90
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:07,075
我看医学报告 你医过多少刺伤
I read the medical reports. How many stab wounds have you treated?

91
00:05:07,110 --> 00:05:09,044
如此说来 要么他不知道自己在干啥
So, either he didn't know what he was doing 

92
00:05:09,045 --> 00:05:10,011
要么就是不想杀他
or he didn't want to kill him.

93
00:05:10,045 --> 00:05:12,514
