给我们点时间 布鲁克曼医生
just give us a moment, Dr... Bruckmann. Oh,

129
00:07:07,789 --> 00:07:09,957
您专门从事老年病学 对吗
you specialize in geriatrics, right?

130
00:07:09,991 --> 00:07:12,159
对 是的 你们在评估我的患者吗
Yes, I do. You're assessing my patient?

131
00:07:12,193 --> 00:07:15,630
他是一桩犯罪的受害者 我是克拉拉马龙医生
He was a victim in a crime. I'm Dr. Clara Malone.

132
00:07:15,664 --> 00:07:18,431
这位是心理犯案组的韦涅夫斯基警探
This is Detective Wisnefski with Psych Crimes Unit.

133
00:07:18,466 --> 00:07:20,667
那么 您是他的精神科医生对吗
So, you're his psychiatrist?

134
00:07:20,701 --> 00:07:23,570
- 但是他 - 很年轻 对 是的
- But he's... - Young. Yes, he is.

135
00:07:23,604 --> 00:07:25,572
我们来这里是因为脸盲
We're here because of the face blindness.

136
00:07:25,606 --> 00:07:28,007
我们希望他能给出些描述
We'd hoped for some kind of a description out of him.

137
00:07:28,041 --> 00:07:30,310
- 对他而言是不可能的 - 我意识到了
- That's not possible for him. - I realize that,

138
00:07:30,344 --> 00:07:32,878
但是他的记忆有些问题
but he has some memory problems.

139
00:07:37,016 --> 00:07:40,319
